The room and bathroom were both clean but our room did not get made up on the second day while we were out.	The shower was a bit cramped, but I think we had one of the smaller rooms.	The room was clean and comfortable and the staff very helpful and friendly.	The rooms are small by American standards, but well appointed, and the bath is excellent.	The bedroom was decorated in a traditional style to suit the building, with pretty glass light fittings, and the bathroom was large with a wet shower area (no bath).	My room was small, but lovely, and the bathroom was large, by European standards.